nodes.title: INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
LLM #2 — STATIC SHOT GENERATOR
Input needed:

Dialogue lines from LLM #1
Reference image description, look at the image of the person to get information for the prompts. Also to get the color skin or ethnicity

Instructions:
For each dialogue line, generate ONE selfie-style or handheld phone shot. Never include the spoken text.
Rules:

Shots must feel like someone filming themselves with a phone
Either: close selfie angle showing their face, or POV shot showing what they see around them
Each shot reintroduces the character from reference image (when visible)
Vary between face shots and environment POV shots
Line 1 = establishing the scene (can be selfie introducing the location)
Keep it natural, handheld feeling
No dialogue text in any prompt
All prompt should start with "Next shot :", except the first one

START DIRECTLY WITH SHOTS:
A selfie shot of a young man white with messy dark hair and glasses in a red hoodie (as in the reference image) holding his phone at arm's length in a gym, chrome equipment and fluorescent lights visible behind him
Next shot: A close selfie angle of the same young white man's strained face trying to lift a dumbbell, the phone held in one trembling hand while gym mirrors blur in the background
Next shot: A handheld POV shot from the young man's perspective looking down at a treadmill control panel, his red hoodie sleeve visible at the edge of frame as the speed number blinks
Next shot: A low selfie angle of the young man white lying collapsed on a workout bench, filming himself from below with the phone, bright gym ceiling lights and weight racks visible above

⚠️ OUTPUT FORMAT: Write only the prompts, one per line. No bullet points, no dashes, no introductions, no explanations. Just the raw prompt text with a single line break between each prompt. Every prompt must be a complete sentence ending with a period.

nodes.title: INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
LLM #1 — DIALOGUE GENERATORInput needed:

Context (e.g., "A guy in a gym talking about working out")
Number of lines (e.g., 4)
Instructions:Write exactly N short, funny spoken lines in first person.Rules:

Always first person ("I...", "I'm...", "I can't...")
Conversational tone, like talking directly to the camera/phone
One sentence per line, under 12 words
First line must establish the scene clearly
Humor comes from the situation
No narration, no storytelling
Example Output:I only joined this gym for the smoothie bar.
I lifted once and now I can't lift my arms.
This treadmill feels like it's chasing me.
If I collapse, tell people I died a hero.


⚠️ OUTPUT FORMAT: Write only the prompts, one per line. No bullet points, no dashes, no introductions, no explanations. Just the raw prompt text with a single line break between each prompt. Every prompt must be a complete sentence ending with a period.

nodes.title: INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
LLM #3 — VIDEO PROMPT GENERATOR
Input needed:

Static shots from LLM #2
Dialogue lines from LLM #1 (for mood reference only—never write them in prompts)

Instructions:
Convert each static shot into a video shot with natural handheld motion.
Rules:

Add realistic handheld camera shake and movement
Add natural gestures (phone moving, person adjusting grip, turning camera)
For POV shots: slight hand movement, camera adjusting angle
For selfie shots: natural arm wobble, person shifting position
Keep it feeling authentic like real phone footage
Never include spoken dialogue text

Example Output:
A selfie video of the young man with messy dark hair and glasses in a red hoodie (as in the reference image) holding his phone at arm's length in the gym, his arm slightly wobbling as he turns the camera to show the equipment behind him
A close selfie angle as he attempts to lift the dumbbell with his other hand, the phone shaking from the strain while his face contorts with effort
A handheld POV video from his perspective looking down at the treadmill controls, the phone gently swaying as his finger reaches into frame to press a button and the speed numbers change
A low selfie angle lying on the workout bench, the phone tilting slightly in his hand as his chest rises and falls with heavy breathing, gym lights flickering above

⚠️ OUTPUT FORMAT: Write only the prompts, one per line. No bullet points, no dashes, no introductions, no explanations. Just the raw prompt text with a single line break between each prompt. Every prompt must be a complete sentence ending with a period.

widgets_values:
LLM #4 — VOICE DESCRIPTOR
Input needed:

Dialogue lines from LLM #1
Context

Instructions:
Describe the speaker's voice in one short line for TTS selection.
Rules:

Include: tone, pitch, pace, personality
Maximum one sentence

Example Output:
Male voice, mid-range, casual and slightly exhausted, with deadpan comedic timing.
